  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nTruffle Contract instances let you do `instance.sendTransaction({...})` to easily send an arbitrary transaction to the instance; this is useful, for instance, for deliberately invoking the contract's fallback or receive functions.  However there's no corresponding `instance.estimateGas({...})` for if you just want a gas estimate.  There's also no `instance.call({...})`, although it's not clear how useful that would be, as the return value would necessarily have to be undecoded hex.  Still, likely we should support it as well.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.5.23",
